[src:minitest/list-of-unit-testing-frameworks-p01] This is a list of notable test automation frameworks commonly used for unit testing.
[src:minitest/list-of-unit-testing-frameworks-p01] Such frameworks are not limited to unit-level testing; they can be used for integration and system level testing.
[src:minitest/list-of-unit-testing-frameworks-p01] For unit testing, a framework must be the same language as the source code under test, and therefore, grouping frameworks by language is valuable.
[src:minitest/list-of-unit-testing-frameworks-p01] For example, .NET groups frameworks that work for any language supported for .NET, and HTTP groups frameworks that test an HTTP server regardless of the implementation language on the server.
[src:minitest/list-of-unit-testing-frameworks-p01] The columns in the tables below are described here.
[src:minitest/list-of-unit-testing-frameworks-p01] Some columns do not apply to some groupings and are therefore omitted from that groupings table.
[src:minitest/list-of-unit-testing-frameworks-p01] For unit testing frameworks for VB.NET, see .NET languages.
[src:minitest/list-of-unit-testing-frameworks-p01] Is JUnit 4.x style, easy, modular and flexible.
[src:minitest/list-of-unit-testing-frameworks-p01] It can be used in resource constrained environments, e.g., embedded software development, and PCs, workstations, servers (Windows and Unix).
[src:minitest/list-of-unit-testing-frameworks-p01] Used in the Apache Portable Runtime Library.
